# .gitattributes — merge drivers for collision-free parallel authoring.
#
# ── Append-only registry/manifest files: merge=union (temperloop#321) ─────────
# These files are pure-append, ORDER-INDEPENDENT registries: every reader
# resolves an entry by set-membership or longest-glob-wins, never by line
# order. Two same-level sibling PRs that each append a DISTINCT entry would,
# under git's default 3-way merge, textually conflict at the shared end-of-file
# insertion point — a hunk collision that costs a rebase-respawn even though the
# two appends are semantically independent (the recurring cost #320 named for
# check slots and #321 generalized to any append-only shared file). The `union`
# merge driver resolves that class by KEEPING BOTH SIDES' added lines, so the
# two appends auto-merge with no rebase.
#
# Safety: `union` only alters CONFLICTING hunks — a clean (non-overlapping)
# merge is untouched — so every existing entry still validates exactly as
# before; the change is purely additive. Scoped deliberately to files whose
# consumer is order-independent AND whose only mutation is append. NOT applied
# to shrink-only ratchets (docs/features/backfill-exempt.txt, whose entries are
# DELETED as docs land — union's keep-both semantics would resurrect a deleted
# line), nor to any code/table file where line order or a genuine same-line edit
# carries meaning (there, a real merge SHOULD surface — see #321's check-slot
# leg, solved by name-keying instead).
docs/features/feature-manifest.txt                                merge=union
workflows/scripts/kernel/kernel-manifest.txt                      merge=union
workflows/scripts/kernel/personal-token-denylist-exempt-files.txt merge=union
workflows/scripts/config/knob-registry-exempt-files.txt           merge=union
